I've already finished milking this one. Let's look
for another cow.\n<Serena>
Like this, like this, like this.\n<Serena>
Like this, like this, like this\n<Serena>

Hmm... I've only ever seen milk in a container, so
I had only recognized it as such from the
beginning...\n<Serena>

Somehow, I feel strange. I may no longer be able
to drink milk with the same indifference as
before.\n<Serena>

Is that so? For us, it's the opposite; we don't
feel anything anymore.\n<Farmer>

Well, originally it's something a mother cow gives
to her calf to drink.\n<Farmer>

The fact that we humans milk them and drink it
ourselves is, when you think about it, quite a
strange tale.\n<Farmer>

Wonder who was the first to think of drinking
it...\n<Farmer>
A mother, to her child...\n<Serena>
Hm? So does this cow have a child?\n<Serena>

That's right. Dairy cows are almost always
pregnant, you know.\n<Farmer>
Pregnant...?? What does that have to do with milk?\n<Serena>

Ha, what a peculiar young lady. You must have been
really sheltered.\n<Farmer>

You see, a mother cow produces milk from her
udders to feed her calf.\n<Farmer>

In other words, they start producing milk only
after having a calf.\n<Farmer>

Using this creature's habits, us clever humans
have the cows stay pregnant all year round so they
keep producing milk.\n<Farmer>
Huh... Hmm...\n<Serena>

Is it that strange to you? After all, not just
cows but all mammals do that.\n<Farmer>

Even you were sucking on your mother's milk until
just the other day, weren't you?\n<Farmer>
Humans too!?\n<Serena>

Of course. There isn't a human who grew up without
sucking on their mother's milk.\n<Farmer>
I have never done such a thing...\n<Serena>

...No, now that I think about it vaguely... I have
memories of clinging to my wet nurse's breast...\n<Serena>

...So when a child is born, will the lord also
produce milk?\n<Serena>
Me? Ah-hahaha!!\n<Farmer>
Hm...?\n<Serena>
Nah, I won't. Producing milk is the mother's job.\n<Farmer>

If anything, it would be your job, not mine. The
job of producing milk, that is.\n<Farmer>
Me!?\n<Serena>
Like this...?\n<Serena>

Humans and cows have different breast sizes. It
shouldn't be with such force.\n<Farmer>
Is that so...\n<Serena>

Well, think of it as practice for someday. Go on
and give it a try.\n<Farmer>

When you say it like that, it makes it even harder
to do...\n<Serena>
\n<Serena>...

\n<Farmer>No need for any more instructions, huh? You've
gotten quite used to this.
セレナ HK_FM01-1
セレナ HK_FM01-1

Even if I'm used to it, I'm only working at half
the speed of you, Master.\n<Serena>
Well, that's because I make my living off of this.\n<Farmer>

Alright, I'm done here. Can I leave the last two
to you?\n<Farmer>

\n<Farmer>I'll make sure to speak well of you to the guild
too.

\n<Farmer>...If possible, I'd like another excellent
adventurer like you to come help again.

\n<Serena>That is... I apologize, but I am also in a hurry,
so I cannot make any promises.

\n<Serena>However, if circumstances allow, I shall visit
again.

\n<Serena>There's a difference between horses and cows, but
it was fun to interact with animals after such a
long time...

\n<Farmer>Heh heh. Is that so, is that so. Well then, I'll

\n<Serena>Ah. Until then.
